did.abstract: The Philosophy of Science Association (PSA) Records document the professional engagements and administrative business of the Philosophy of Science Association, an organization founded in 1933 to further the study and discussion of subjects related to the philosophy of science. The Philosophy of Science Association promotes research, teaching, and free discussion of issues in the philosophy of science from diverse standpoints. To this end, the PSA engages in activities such as: the publishing of periodicals, essays and monographs; sponsoring conventions and meetings; and awarding prizes for distinguished work in the field.
did.langmaterial: The material in this collection is in English.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: The Philosophy of Science Association Records contain records that document the administration of the Philosophy of Science Association between 1959-2005. The collection includes planning documents regarding the Association's Biennial meetings, governing board correspondence and election material, financial records, membership information and grants. Also included are article submissions, copyright documentation and correspondence regarding the Philosophy of Science journal, which was first published in 1934.

bioghist.head: History
bioghist.p: Founded in 1933, the Philosophy of Science Association (PSA) promotes research, teaching, and free discussion of issues in the philosophy of science from diverse standpoints. To this end, the PSA engages in activities such as: the publishing of periodicals, essays and monographs; sponsoring conventions and meetings; and awarding prizes for distinguished work in the field.

The Philosophy of Science Association was first announced in the Journal of Philosophy, December 1933: "We welcome the first number of a new philosophical quarterly, entitled Philosophy of Science. It is the 'chief external expression' of the Philosophy of Science Association." (vol. 30, no. 25. p. 700) The first editorial board for the new journal was composed of William Malisoff (as editor), Eric T. Bell, Albert E. Blumberg, Rudolf Carnap, Morris R. Cohen, W. W. Cook, Herbert Feigl, K. S. Lashley, Henry Margenau, H. J. Muller, L. Susan Stebbing, Dirk J. Struik, and Alexander Weinstein. The first issue of Philosophy of Science appeared in January 1934, and was shepherded not just by the editorial board, but also by more than 40 other advisory board members, including P.W. Bridgman, R.A. Fischer, M. Polanyi, H. Reichenbach, George Sarton, E. A. Singer, jr., H. Urey, and E. Wigner.

Early activities of the PSA included co- sponsorship of the Fifth International Congress for the Unity of Science, held at Harvard in September 5-10, 1939. Other sponsors included the International Committee of the Congresses for the Unity of Science, the International Institute for the Unity of Science, the American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS), the Association for Symbolic Logic, and the American Philosophical Association. After World War II, the PSA began to meet annually at December AAAS meetings, in conjunction and cooperation with Section L (History and Philosophy of Science) of the AAAS. In addition to organizing symposia on philosophy of science at AAAS, the PSA began to conduct its business of governance at these meetings. It passed its first set of by-laws at the 1946 meeting, which would be revised in 1947, and then finally published in 1948 in Philosophy of Science.

According to its by-laws, the PSA was dedicated to "furthering of the study and discussion of the subject of philosophy of science, broadly interpreted, and the encouragement of practical consequences which may flow therefrom of benefit to scientists and philosophers in particular and to men of good will in general." (Phil. Sci. 1948, vol. 15, p. 176) In addition, the 1947 by- laws state that the PSA was to meet annually. For the next fifteen years, notices of the annual meetings were placed in "News and Notices" in Philosophy of Science every October for the meeting that was held in December, in conjunction with Section L of AAAS.

PSA president Adolf Gr√ºnbaum organized the first stand-alone biennial meeting of PSA in 1968, held in Pittsburgh, PA. This began the tradition of biennial meetings and became enshrined in PSA by-laws in 1970. The next meeting was held in Boston, MA in October 1970, and because of the death of Rudolf Carnap in September 1970, it was held in Carnap's honor. Those proceedings were published by the Boston Studies Series in Philosophy of Science (vol. VIII), edited by Roger Buck and Robert Cohen, and were the first published PSA proceedings.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Biennial meetings series documents the Philosophy of Science's biennial meetings from 1968-1996. Files are labeled by meeting year and site and contain correspondence, financial planning documents, book display planning documents, program design and hotel information.

did.unittitle: 1978 (San Francisco) Sixth Biennial Meeting Ads and Book Displays

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Related Professional Organizations series contains information about other professional scientific and philosophical organizations which the PSA engaged in cooperative and specialized project work between 1972-1996. Files are labeled by the name of the organization and includes the American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS), American Philosophical Association (APA), Institute for the Unity of Science, International Federation of Philosophical Societies, International Union for the History and Philosophy of Science, National Endowment for the Humanities, National Science Foundation and the Philosophy Journal Editor's Association.

did.unittitle: American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS)

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS) subseries contains memos and correspondence related to developments within the AAAS that were distributed to affiliate organizations, which included the Philosophy of Science Association. Information includes new publications, collaborative and learning opportunities and updates on leadership changes. Also included are meeting minutes of the AAAS board along with minutes from larger AAAS Coalition meetings between affiliate organizations. Files are arranged chronologically by year.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The American Philosophical Association (APA) subseries contains memos and correspondence related to collaboration between the APA and the Philosophy of Science Association. As an affiliate member, the APA often assisted the PSA in sharing employment opportunities for scientific philosophers, collaboration in journal publishing and joint cooperation in the development of the Conference of Philosophical Societies. Files are organized chronologically by year.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Association of Philosophy Journal Editors subseries contains minutes and correspondence created by the board Association of Philosophy Journal Editors Association, of which the Philosophy of Science Association was a member. Issues addressed in the work of the Association include proper editing and management of philosophical journals along with communication and collaborative efforts between Philosophical organizations to promote common professional standards in philosophical journal publishing.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Institute for the Unity of Science subseries contains correspondence, financial and legal documents regarding the incorporation of the Philosophy of Science association with the Institute for the Unity of Science (IUS), which was formed by Otto Neurath after the conclusion of the Eighth International Congress of Philosophy held in Prague in September of 1934. The IUS attempted to organize congresses and related activities that furthered the work of logical empricism developed by the Vienna Circle and engage in inter-scientific discussion groups with philosophers from around the world.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: International Federation of Philosophical Societies: The International Federation of Philosophical Societies (IFPS) subseries contains correspondence regarding the Philosophy of Science Association's participation in the IFPS's efforts to serve as a coordinating agency for philosophical societies to promote international cooperation and host a quinquennial International Congress of Philosophy.

did.unittitle: International Union for the History and Philosophy of Science

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The International Union for the History and Philosophy of Science subseries contains correspondence and memos regarding the Philosophy of Science Association's participation in the International Union for the History and Philosophy of Science. Information includes the PSA's affiliation and involvement in the group which included the selection of delegates from the PSA to attend the Union's General Assembly along with the PSA's work on the United States National Committee. The main activities of the Union are the two quadriennial congresses organized by the two divisions: the International Congress for History of Science and Technology (ICHST) and the Congress for Logic, Methodology and Philosophy of Science and Technology (CLMPST).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The National Endowment for the Humanities series includes correspondence that documents effort by the Philosophy of Science Association to secure NEH grant funding for research in scientific philosophy and to better promote NEH opportunities to PSA members through newsletter announcements and other correspondence. Files are arranged chronologically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The National Science Foundation subseries includes grant applications and proposals for National Science Foundation travel and research grants applied for by by Philosophy of Science Association members. Files are organized by year.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Joint Newsletters subseries contains correspondence regarding the proposed development of a joint newsletter in cooperation between the PSA and the Society for the History of Technology (SHOT), Society for the Social Studies of Science (4S) and History and Sociology of Science (HSS). The subseries also includes correspondence held within the PSA about involvement and relationships with other organizations such as ACLS (American Council of Learned Societies), FISP (International Federation of Philosophical Societies) and The American Catholic Philosophical Association.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Copyright and Permissions for Publishing series contains copyright and publishing release forms completed by authors in the Philosophy of Science journal between 1958-1994.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Offices and Officials series contains administrative documents and correspondence kept by elected officers of the Philosophy of Science Association ranging from 1970-1994. Files are labeled by name of the officer and include PSA Presidents, Secretaries, Chairpersons and Journal Editors in Chief. Issues documented in the correspondence include the management of the Philosophy of Science Journal, communication with other professional scientific and philosophical organizations, and administrative issues in the PSA.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Journal Management series documentation of issues regarding the Philosophy of Science Journal between 1970 and 1996. Files include editorial board correspondence, Editor in Chief selection processes, journal inventories and issues and complaints raised about the contents of the journal.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Governing Board series documents the activities and proceedings of the PSA Governing Board between 1970-1996. Files include minutes, correspondence and meeting documentation created by the Governing Board as well as documentation of the development of the Association's constitution and bylaws.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Travel Grants series contains documentation of Travel Grants awarded to membership for the Biennial Meetings of the Philosophy of Science Association between 1994-1995.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence series contains communications created by members of the Philosophy of Science Association regarding administrative issues between 1974-1997. The bulk of the series is comprised of printed documentation of the communications created by the PSA's e-mail server.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Election Files series contains documentation of elections held for the PSA Governing Board between 1972-1995. The series also contains meeting notes and correspondence created by the Nominating Committee in relation to the planning and conducting of board elections.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Joint Conferences series contains documentation of conferences held in conjunction with other professional scientific and philosophical organizations and the PSA between 1977-1982. Conferences include the PSA Critical Research Problems Conference, Science and Technology Studies and Ethics and Values in Science and Technology held in conjunction with the National Science Foundation.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Financial Records series contains financial documentation kept in relation to the administration of the Philosophy of Science Association between 1974-1996. Files include journal publishing finances, tax information and non-profit status reports.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Directories series contains membership directories and PSA Governing Board listings between 1987-1996.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Newsletters series contains issues of the official PSA membership newsletter distributed between 1976 and 1990. Newsletters often contained reporting on PSA business and newsworthy items regarding individual PSA members, as well as information regarding upcoming biennial meetings.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series XV. Journal Issues contains published copies of the PSA Journal, ranging from 1959-1961.

did.unittitle: Biennial Meeting Papers and Symposia Submissions

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series XV. Biennial Meetings Papers and Symposia Submissions contains contributed papers and symposia which were presented at the Philosophy of Science Association's Biennial Meeting. Papers were also published in the Philosophy of Science Journal following their presentation at the meeting. Submission files for contributed papers and symposia are filed similarly to Philosophy of Science Journal files and are labeled by last name and title. Each file contains an acceptance or rejection letter as well as correspondence, edited drafts and proofs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series XVI. Journal Submission Files contains submission information for articles to be published in the Journal of Scientific Philosophy. A large portion of the collection is comprised of files relating to the organization and publication of the Philosophy of Science Association Journal, including drafts, memos, correspondence, and proofs of papers. Files are organized by submission date and labeled by submitting author's name, title of the paper and the number issued to the paper by the PSA office.
